Just hours out from arguably the biggest match of his career, Roger Federer gifted Omar Jasika an opportunity the young Aussie will never forget. 
 
Sunday night&apos;s Australian Open final between Federer and Rafael Nadal is being touted as the biggest in the tournament&apos;s 105-year history. 

And as Federer hit the practice court for a final tune-up before the blockbuster match, he asked Jasika to be his hitting partner. 

